requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.

issues.description: The term 'PMS' is not defined. It could refer to 'Patient Monitoring System' or another system.
issues.suggested_fix: Define 'PMS' explicitly in the requirements glossary or replace with the full system name.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a port for the pod that records [pulse|pressure|oximeter|telemetry leads].

issues.description: Requirements specify ports for different pod types but don't describe how these ports differ or how pods are identified/connected.
issues.suggested_fix: Add details about port identification, physical specifications, or pod detection mechanism.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not trigger alarms when the patient's vitals are within the ranges that hospital personnel defined.

issues.description: Implied negation of REQ-016 creates potential ambiguity in alarm logic (e.g., what happens during sensor failures?).
issues.suggested_fix: Combine with REQ-016 into a single requirement clarifying all alarm conditions.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LCD screen shall show the EGG strip in a green color (using hexadecimal color code: #00FF00).

issues.description: 'EGG' is likely a typo for 'ECG' (electrocardiogram), which is used elsewhere in requirements.
issues.suggested_fix: Correct to 'ECG' for consistency with REQ-011.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall make an audible noise that is between 50 and 60 decibels when an alarm is triggered.

issues.description: Decibel range is specified but lacks context (distance from device, measurement standard).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify measurement conditions (e.g., 'measured at 1 meter in a quiet room').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall send record updates to the Patient Records System database...

issues.description: REQ-033 mentions 'EMR' while sub-requirements reference 'Patient Records System'. These may refer to the same system but use different terms.
issues.suggested_fix: Standardize terminology to either 'EMR' or 'Patient Records System' throughout.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not receive software updates when connected to a patient.

issues.description: 'Connected to a patient' is vague. Does this mean when pods are attached? When vitals are being monitored?
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the condition (e.g., 'when any pod is actively transmitting data').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall continue processing health data from pods (sensors) even when it is disconnected from the dock.

issues.description: No duration is specified for how long processing should continue on battery power.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify expected runtime or link to battery life requirements (REQ-030).

domain_model_issues.description: Pod lacks attributes differentiating types mentioned in REQ-003.1 to REQ-003.4 (pulse, pressure, etc.).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'type' attribute or subclass Pod for each sensor type.

domain_model_issues.description: Association doesn't reflect the 14-Pin connector requirement (REQ-003) or multiple port types.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add connector/port as an association class or refine relationship description.

domain_model_issues.description: No class/method for handling alarm sound generation as required by REQ-025.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'Alarm' class or method 'generateAudibleAlarm()' to System.

domain_model_issues.description: Attribute doesn't enumerate allowed values (English, Spanish, French per REQ-028.1).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add constraint or use enum type with allowed values.

domain_model_issues.description: No attributes/methods to handle EMR compatibility (REQ-034) or data fields from REQ-033.x.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods for receiving updates and attributes for EMR type.

domain_model_issues.description: No representation of compliance standards (NFPA, OSHA, HIPAA from REQ-037 to REQ-039).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'Compliance' class or document as system constraints.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for handling battery low state and notifications
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall display a low battery warning when battery life falls below 15% and shall automatically save all current data to persistent storage.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical for patient safety and data integrity during battery depletion. Current requirements don't specify behavior during low battery conditions.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for alarm escalation when vitals remain out of range
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: If patient vitals remain outside defined ranges for more than 2 minutes, the system shall escalate the alarm by increasing volume to 70dB and flashing the LCD display.
missing_requirements.rationale: Medical best practices require escalation for persistent critical conditions. Current requirements only cover initial alarm triggering.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data encryption during transmission
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All data transmitted to Patient Records System and Central Patient-monitoring System shall be encrypted using AES-256 encryption.
missing_requirements.rationale: HIPAA compliance requires encryption of protected health information during transmission. While HIPAA compliance is mentioned, specific technical requirements are missing.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system initialization and self-test
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Upon power-up, the system shall perform a complete self-test of all components including pod connectivity, display functionality, and network connectivity, and shall display test results on the LCD.
missing_requirements.rationale: Medical devices typically require power-on self-tests to ensure proper functioning. This is missing from current requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for handling pod disconnection
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: If a pod becomes disconnected during monitoring, the system shall immediately display a visual warning on the LCD and sound a distinct 55dB alarm different from vital range alarms.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical for patient safety to alert staff when monitoring capability is compromised. Current requirements don't address pod connectivity issues.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data retention policy
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically purge locally stored data older than 72 hours, except when such data is associated with an active alarm event, which shall be retained for 30 days.
missing_requirements.rationale: Important for managing storage capacity while meeting medical record retention requirements. Current requirements only mention 24-hour storage without retention policy.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All system configuration changes (including vital range definitions) shall require authentication via hospital ID badge swipe or username/password with minimum 8-character complexity.
missing_requirements.rationale: Prevents unauthorized changes to critical monitoring parameters. Current requirements allow range changes without specifying access control.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system clock synchronization
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall synchronize its internal clock with the hospital NTP server when connected to the LAN, and maintain time accuracy within ±1 second when disconnected.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical for accurate timestamping of medical events. Time synchronization is fundamental but not mentioned in current requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for display brightness adjustment
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LCD shall automatically adjust brightness based on ambient light conditions, with manual override capability for clinical staff.
missing_requirements.rationale: Important for usability in varying lighting conditions of hospital environments. Display colors are specified but not brightness control.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require explicit acknowledgement of alarms by clinical staff via physical button press, and shall log all acknowledgement events with timestamps.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensures staff awareness of critical alerts. Current requirements don't specify how alarms are acknowledged or tracked.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system status indicators
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LCD shall continuously display clear visual indicators for: network connectivity status, battery level, pod connectivity status, and alarm system status.
missing_requirements.rationale: Critical for at-a-glance assessment of system health. Current requirements focus on patient data display but not system status.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall validate all incoming pod data for reasonable ranges (heart rate 20-250 bpm, SpO2 50-100%, etc.) before processing or display, and flag questionable readings for clinician review.
missing_requirements.rationale: Prevents display of physiologically impossible values that could cause false alarms. Current requirements don't address data validation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for fail-safe operation during software updates
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: During software updates, the system shall maintain continuous monitoring functionality using the previous version's software, and shall only apply updates after verifying they don't compromise critical monitoring features.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensures patient safety isn't compromised during updates. Current requirements prohibit updates during patient connection but don't specify fail-safe mechanisms.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall maintain an encrypted log of all system events including: alarm triggers, configuration changes, user logins, and system errors, retaining these logs for minimum 90 days.
missing_requirements.rationale: Important for compliance and troubleshooting. While HIPAA is mentioned, specific logging requirements are absent.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for patient identification verification
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When first connected to a patient, the system shall require confirmation of patient identity by scanning a wristband barcode or manually entering at least two patient identifiers matching hospital records.
missing_requirements.rationale: Prevents wrong-patient errors in monitoring. Unique identifier exists but process for associating it with correct patient is missing.
